Sometimes a hurdle comes my way and I must find a way to jump it. Other times I look for a way to minimize it first before jumping it. I can't walk around it because I'd lose momentum and speed. I'd also lose the satisfaction of tackling the hurdle head-on. And then, the competition, they want to win the race as much as I do. They will do things to get in my way and thwart my victory.
